item.title: My compiler doesnt work
item.dc:creator: @Rockin Rockin
item.description:
@Rockin wrote:

I can’t really help you unless you post what it looks like (Right click->edit with notepad)

But I use this:

@echo off COLOR 09 title Compiler "C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.6.0_Your JDK version here\bin\javac.exe" -cp . *.java pause

Notice, the “Your JDK version here”, replace it with your version. (Find in C:\Program Files\Java)

item.title: My compiler doesnt work
item.dc:creator: @Goran Goran
item.description:
@Goran wrote:

[quote=“pkn00b, post:1, topic:265169”]My compiler says it has compiled, but it doesent work.
what should I do?[/quote]
replace it with this====

@echo off
if exist “%programfiles%\Java” (call :compile “%programfiles%\Java”) else (goto error)
:compile
for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe")
if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java)
if defined p (goto end)
:error
echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load.
“%programfiles%\Internet Explorer\iexplore.exe” http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
:end
echo Finished!
pause
exit
